instruction:
Simplify the radical expression:
$$
\frac{ 4 \cdot \sqrt{2 \cdot n} }{ \sqrt{16 \cdot n^4} }
$$

Options:
A. \frac{\sqrt{2}}{n^{\frac{1}{4}}}
B. \frac{\sqrt{2}}{n^{\frac{1}{3}}}
C. \frac{\sqrt{2}}{n^{\frac{4}{2}}}
D. \frac{\sqrt{2}}{n^{\frac{7}{2}}}
E. \frac{\sqrt{2}}{n^{\frac{5}{2}}}
F. \frac{\sqrt{2}}{n^{\frac{2}{2}}}
G. \frac{\sqrt{2}}{n^{\frac{3}{2}}}
H. \frac{\sqrt{2}}{n^{\frac{1}{2}}}
